    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-07T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="121"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName>—<persName corresp="#p_PYT1"
                            >Pyun</persName> Meeting, Geneva, May 7, Morning: The <gloss type="from"
                            >United States Delegation</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in
                            Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-07T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 7, 1954—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. Repeated information Department <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 137
                    Tokyo 27. Re <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 127, repeated <gloss
                        target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> Seoul 50.<note n="1" xml:id="d121fn1">Dated
                        May 7, <ref target="#pg_218">p. 218</ref>.</note> Went over revised draft
                    this morning with <persName corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_YCY1">Yang</persName> and expressed increasingly difficult
                    position here Geneva lacking <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> decision agree
                    on draft proposal. <persName corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_YCY1">Yang</persName> said they had sent several telegrams
                    urging President <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> accept draft. Re
                    elections for President in addition for National Assembly in paragraph II–A
                    revised draft, believe we should delete elections for President. <persName
                        corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_YCY1"
                        >Yang</persName> said <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> del strongly
                    opposed as reported <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 107.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d121fn2">Same as telegram 42, May 5, from Geneva, <ref
                            target="#pg_204">p. 204</ref>.</note> We note from Seoul’s 52<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d121fn3">Same as telegram 1125, May 7, from Seoul, <ref
                            target="#pg_213">p. 213</ref>.</note> to Geneva, Defense Minister has
                    expressed fear election for President would greatly affect morale <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> armed forces. <persName corresp="#p_RWS1"
                        >Robertson</persName> told <persName corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> we
                    fully prepared delete elections for President if <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                        >ROK</gloss> desires.</p>
                <p>Only other change suggested by <persName corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> is in
                    paragraph III–A where he asked insert “unified” in second sentence to read
                    “government of unified Korea”.</p>
                <p>Explained paragraph IV on withdrawal non-Korean forces tentative. <persName
                        corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_YCY1"
                        >Yang</persName> both liked revision.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_YCY1">Yang</persName> informed us privately <persName
                        corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> sending message today to President
                    recommending deletion presidential elections and acceptance revised draft
                    proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
